b2135.textContent: Mechanism of action of caffeine on:

publicationXrefaab.standardName: Caffeine and Clinical Outcomes in Premature Neonates.

comments.content: Caffeine acts as a competitive antagonist at adenosine receptors -- particularly the A and AA subtypes -- thereby promoting wakefulness and modifying the activity of key neurotransmitters, including dopamine, epinephrine, norepinephrine, and serotonin, within the central nervous system.  Inspired by [Figure 1 in Kumar and Lipshultz, 2019](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6915633).
